# Enforce LF line endings for ALL text files on every platform.
#
# This is load-bearing for reproducibility (hostile-audit A10: a Windows-authored
# artifact executed on Linux must not drift). Prompt files and configs are
# hash-addressed; if git rewrote them to CRLF on a Windows checkout, their sha256
# would no longer match prompts/REGISTRY.json and the firewall / config-validation
# gates would fail. Forcing eol=lf keeps the working copy byte-identical to the
# committed blob on all platforms.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicitly binary (never converted, never diffed).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
*.bin binary
*.pt binary
*.onnx binary
*.parquet binary
